html.p: the value was estimated from the HS submodel at steady state. Indeed, taking into account that (i) PC2 is precursors of PC1 [9227501], (ii) life span of PC1 is about 120 days [20616357], (iii) ratio of PC1/PC2 at steady state = 19/37 [7103258] we represented lung cell dynamics system as follows: --(Volalv*kmatpc) --> PC2 --(Volalv*kdifpc*PC2)--> PC1--(Volalv*kapopc1*PC1)-->. Then consider the system at steady state and assuming that lifespan (Tls) corresponds to time required for 99% of cell die we have come to following formulas: (a) kapopc1 = ln(1/0.01)/(120 days) = 1.6e-3 1/h, (b) kdifpc = kapopc1*PC1ss/PC2ss = 8.2e-4 1/h, (c) kmatpc = kdifpc*PC2ss. Since PC2 to PC1 transition was not considered in the version of the model we can assume that kapopc = kdif_pc
